WEBVTT

00:02.461 --> 00:05.756
GREAT DRAGON:
In a land of myth and a time of magic...

00:05.923 --> 00:10.886
...the destiny of a great kingdom
rests on the shoulders of a young man.

00:11.053 --> 00:14.473
His name: Merlin.

00:22.189 --> 00:24.024
[WIND BLOWING]

00:41.917 --> 00:44.503
Halt! Stay where you are.

00:52.719 --> 00:55.931
- Where are you headed?
WOMAN: The Seas of Meredor.

00:58.850 --> 00:59.893
What's in the cart?

01:06.066 --> 01:07.192
Lady Morgana.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.130
MORGANA:
Are you all right?

01:28.297 --> 01:32.175
Yes, thank you, sister.
But we must hurry.

01:32.342 --> 01:37.848
Night is nearly upon us,
and we still have far to go.

02:19.014 --> 02:20.307
Sorry.

02:25.395 --> 02:27.105
[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

02:31.693 --> 02:33.153
What are you doing in my kitchen?

02:33.320 --> 02:35.822
Uh, the prince's shirt.

02:36.531 --> 02:40.744
Keep your dirty fingers off my food.
Do you understand?

02:53.590 --> 02:55.217
[MOUTHS]
Go. Go.

02:55.384 --> 02:57.219
COOK:
Oil

03:06.978 --> 03:08.772
LANCELOT:
You could try a bit of salt.

03:09.606 --> 03:13.276
MERLIN: Arthur is going to kill me.
LANCELOT: Let's see.

03:14.736 --> 03:18.407
-You've faced far worse, Merlin.
-He needs it for tonight.

03:18.573 --> 03:21.451
I'm sure a man of your talents
can think of something.

03:23.120 --> 03:24.996
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

03:37.300 --> 03:41.471
-You're dressed.
-Yes, Merlin. I'm not an idiot.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.516
[MERLIN CHUCKLES]

03:44.683 --> 03:47.102
-Are you sure about that?
- Ibeg your pardon?

03:47.269 --> 03:50.147
-It's just that--
-Merlin, I am trying to write a speech.

03:50.313 --> 03:51.690
-Do you want help?
-No.

03:51.857 --> 03:56.027
You won't want this then.
| spent all night working on it.

04:05.370 --> 04:07.831
-What do you think?
-It needs a polish.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.583
I'll add it to the list.

04:11.793 --> 04:15.589
Merlin, there aren't many servants
who get the chance to write a prince's speech.

04:15.756 --> 04:18.257
Obviously it would be too much
for you to say thank you.

04:29.227 --> 04:31.563
The Isle of the Blessed.

04:54.085 --> 04:56.630
You know where we wish to go.

05:18.735 --> 05:20.821
You've not eaten, sire.

05:22.113 --> 05:23.698
Sire.

05:38.171 --> 05:39.881
It doesn't seem to make any difference.

05:40.841 --> 05:44.469
I'm not sure it ever will,
but at least it gives him peace.

05:46.304 --> 05:50.225
It's been a year since Morgana betrayed him.

05:50.725 --> 05:54.813
His heart is broken and his spirit is gone.

05:59.985 --> 06:01.570
You're joining us for the feast tonight?

06:01.736 --> 06:04.489
| don't think so. I need to stay with the king.

06:05.448 --> 06:06.825
You're very good to him, Gwen.

06:08.034 --> 06:12.080
| don't do it for him. I do it for Arthur.

06:27.929 --> 06:30.056
[WYVERN SCREECHING]

06:30.265 --> 06:31.933
[HORSE WHINNIES]

06:36.813 --> 06:38.064
LEON:
The reports are true, sire.

06:38.815 --> 06:41.693
We caught up with Morgana
on the Plains of Denaria.

06:41.860 --> 06:44.654
-Was she alone?
-There was someone else.

06:44.821 --> 06:46.448
ARTHUR: Morgause?
ELYAN: Couldn't be sure.

06:46.615 --> 06:49.159
-Where was Morgana heading?
-The Seas of Meredor.

06:49.826 --> 06:51.411
Isle of the Blessed.

06:55.040 --> 06:58.043
-I'll send out patrols at first light.
ARTHUR: Thank you, Agravaine.

06:58.209 --> 07:01.129
Sire, you should know,
her powers have grown.

07:02.839 --> 07:04.966
Sir Bertrand and Sir Montague
are both dead.

07:09.012 --> 07:10.805
Keep me informed of any developments.

07:16.895 --> 07:19.314
For months, nothing. Why now?

07:19.481 --> 07:22.692
We knew she couldn't stay hidden forever.
Today, tomorrow, what does it matter?

07:24.361 --> 07:26.529
Mustn't live in fear, Arthur.

07:26.696 --> 07:31.701
Camelot is strong. If Morgana were to act,
we'd be ready for her.

07:33.495 --> 07:35.288
You're right, of course.

07:36.623 --> 07:39.834
| don't know how I would have got through
these last few months without you.

07:41.378 --> 07:42.963
Thank you, uncle.

07:44.965 --> 07:46.299
| made a promise to your mother.

07:48.551 --> 07:49.803
I'll always be there for you.

07:56.101 --> 07:57.852
[WYVERN SCREECHING]

08:17.956 --> 08:20.208
[CHATTERING]

08:24.129 --> 08:25.839
Samhain.

08:27.257 --> 08:31.594
It is the time of year when we feel closest
to the spirits of our ancestors.

08:32.261 --> 08:35.265
It is a time to remember those we have lost...

08:35.807 --> 08:38.351
...to celebrate their passing.

08:42.438 --> 08:45.025
MORGAUSE:
Sambhain is almost upon us.

08:45.191 --> 08:46.651
We must hurry.

08:49.696 --> 08:51.698
| can't do this.

08:52.741 --> 08:53.783
Sister.

08:56.578 --> 08:58.955
Remember what I've told you.

08:59.122 --> 09:01.458
It is the only way.

09:02.333 --> 09:08.590
What you are about to do
will affect everyone, even you.

09:09.758 --> 09:14.012
But most importantly,
it will bring our enemies to their knees.

09:16.639 --> 09:19.642
You must be strong and remember that.

09:31.279 --> 09:32.447
Do not be scared.

09:40.830 --> 09:43.583
| am not long for this world.

09:44.709 --> 09:46.920
There is nothing left for me here now.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.468
Please, sister.

09:55.929 --> 09:58.681
Let my parting be my final gift to you.

10:13.154 --> 10:14.280
To the king.

10:14.447 --> 10:15.782
[BELL TOLLS]

10:18.368 --> 10:22.372
[MORGANA SPEAKING
IN ANCIENT LANGUAGE]

10:33.633 --> 10:34.884
[GASPS]

10:37.470 --> 10:39.180
[MUFFLED]
To the king.

10:39.931 --> 10:41.766
[MUFFLED]
To the king.

10:42.767 --> 10:45.228
[CREATURE SHRIEKING]

11:00.743 --> 11:02.495
Emrys.

11:03.079 --> 11:04.831
Emrys.

11:05.498 --> 11:07.667
Emrys.

11:09.794 --> 11:12.213
[CHATTERING]

11:21.097 --> 11:22.807
[SHIVERING]

11:48.958 --> 11:50.043
Who are you?

11:50.919 --> 11:55.131
| am the Cailleach,
the gatekeeper to the spirit world.

11:57.258 --> 12:00.386
You have torn the veil between the worlds.

12:02.972 --> 12:06.267
[VOICES SCREAMING AND WAILING]

12:07.227 --> 12:08.478
The Dorocha.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.190
They are the voices of the dead, my child.

12:13.441 --> 12:15.401
And like the dead, they are numberless.

12:18.488 --> 12:20.949
You are right to be afraid, Morgana.

12:21.658 --> 12:24.911
Your enemies will rue this day
and all the destruction it brings...

12:25.078 --> 12:26.454
...but you must beware.

12:27.413 --> 12:31.251
Tearing the veil between the worlds
has created a new world.

12:31.709 --> 12:34.545
And you will not walk through it alone.

12:35.129 --> 12:39.676
The one they call Emrys
will walk in your shadow.

12:39.926 --> 12:41.052
He is your destiny.

12:44.013 --> 12:46.724
And he is your doom.

12:49.560 --> 12:50.603
CAILLEACH [WHISPERS]:
Emrys.

12:52.522 --> 12:55.108
-What happened?
- I don't know.

12:55.275 --> 12:58.653
-I've never felt anyone so cold before.
-Will he be all right?

12:59.070 --> 13:02.365
I'll need hawthorne to improve
the blood flow, and blankets.

13:03.783 --> 13:04.993
Lots of blankets.

13:17.130 --> 13:19.757
MERLIN:
When she spoke, her voice...

13:20.383 --> 13:23.511
It was as though it came
from the depths of the earth.

13:24.220 --> 13:25.972
And her eyes...

13:27.807 --> 13:29.726
...they were so sad.

13:30.101 --> 13:32.395
So much pain in them.

13:38.234 --> 13:39.277
Who is she?

13:41.904 --> 13:45.575
The Cailleach.
The gatekeeper to the spirit world.

13:45.742 --> 13:47.243
Why was she there?

13:49.537 --> 13:52.707
It was on the stroke of midnight
of Samhain's eve...

13:53.082 --> 13:57.211
...the very moment when the veil
between the worlds is at its thinnest.

13:57.378 --> 14:00.048
It cannot be a coincidence.

14:00.715 --> 14:04.218
-Why was I the only one to see her?
-You have great power, Merlin.

14:04.385 --> 14:07.138
For someone so gifted,
such visions are not uncommon.

14:07.305 --> 14:09.891
But you don't understand.
It wasn't a vision.

14:10.058 --> 14:12.310
She knew who I was.

14:12.977 --> 14:14.312
She called me Emrys.

14:22.403 --> 14:25.281
What is it? What does it mean?

14:27.200 --> 14:28.242
I'm not sure.

14:30.328 --> 14:33.498
But if someone has torn the veil
between the worlds...

14:34.248 --> 14:35.917
...then God help us all.

14:41.964 --> 14:43.883
[CLATTERING]

14:44.967 --> 14:46.010
Merlin.

14:48.012 --> 14:49.722
-Merlin.
-What?

14:49.889 --> 14:50.932
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:51.099 --> 14:53.226
-Merlin!
-That's not me.

14:54.852 --> 14:56.854
Excuse me, sire.

14:58.815 --> 15:01.484
You're needed in the council chambers
as a matter of urgency.

15:01.692 --> 15:03.361
[WOMAN SOBBING]

15:03.528 --> 15:05.780
ARTHUR: What's happened to her?
-Her village was attacked.

15:05.947 --> 15:08.241
-By who?
-It's not entirely clear, sire.

15:08.408 --> 15:10.159
[SOBBING]

15:12.453 --> 15:15.164
-What's your name?
-Drea.

15:19.544 --> 15:24.006
Drea, I'm Arthur.

15:24.590 --> 15:26.342
Don't be frightened.

15:27.468 --> 15:29.178
Tell me what happened.

15:30.304 --> 15:34.600
My mother, my father,
my little sister, they're--

15:35.643 --> 15:36.811
It's all right.

15:37.395 --> 15:38.980
It's all right.

15:40.356 --> 15:41.649
Someone attacked them.

15:43.484 --> 15:44.944
Who?

15:45.695 --> 15:50.992
There was no one. Just shapes.

15:52.743 --> 15:54.537
You didn't see their faces?

15:55.913 --> 15:58.082
They had no faces.

16:02.670 --> 16:04.714
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

16:04.881 --> 16:06.966
I-- I keep telling you.

16:08.092 --> 16:09.469
They were there, but...

16:10.428 --> 16:12.013
...they weren't there.

16:13.181 --> 16:15.808
They moved so quickly.

16:17.226 --> 16:19.020
It was as if they weren't real, but...

16:20.771 --> 16:22.315
...they must have been.

16:25.151 --> 16:27.028
| could hear the people screaming...

16:27.987 --> 16:31.657
...and then silence.

16:33.034 --> 16:35.912
They were all dead.

16:36.120 --> 16:37.914
[CRYING]

16:39.248 --> 16:41.292
Hey. Thank you.

16:46.339 --> 16:47.882
-Where is this village?
-Howden.

16:48.049 --> 16:49.675
It's to the east of the White Mountains.

16:49.884 --> 16:53.804
-No more than half a day's hard ride.
-Ready the men.

17:12.198 --> 17:13.366
[WOODPECKER TAPPING]

17:13.532 --> 17:16.577
Merlin, you need your comfort blanket?

17:16.743 --> 17:19.288
-What do you mean?
-You're making me edgy.

17:20.330 --> 17:21.374
[HORSE WHINNIES]

17:21.540 --> 17:22.875
That's a horse.

17:23.041 --> 17:26.127
-Maybe it sensed something.
-Yes, that you're a clot-poll.

17:26.295 --> 17:30.883
-That's my word.
-Yeah, and it suits you perfectly.

17:43.479 --> 17:45.147
ARTHUR:
It's too quiet.

18:03.040 --> 18:05.251
[SQUEAKING]

18:23.269 --> 18:24.979
[DOOR CREAKS]

18:25.688 --> 18:27.565
[SCRATCHING]

18:29.775 --> 18:31.444
[BAAS]

19:01.599 --> 19:02.642
[LOUD CRUNCH]

19:04.935 --> 19:06.437
Sorry.

19:07.396 --> 19:08.606
ELYAN:
Here!

19:24.955 --> 19:26.749
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

19:29.543 --> 19:30.878
You saw it?

19:37.885 --> 19:40.304
We are literally chasing shadows.

19:42.890 --> 19:44.392
Come on.

20:04.203 --> 20:06.247
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

20:18.634 --> 20:20.261
[THUD]

20:33.816 --> 20:35.067
[RUSTLING]

20:50.124 --> 20:51.584
[HEN CLUCKING]

20:57.214 --> 20:59.467
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

21:14.356 --> 21:16.442
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

21:27.244 --> 21:28.704
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORD]

21:36.837 --> 21:39.590
[SPEAKING MAGIC WORDS]

21:41.467 --> 21:42.510
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

21:50.601 --> 21:52.520
[LOUD SHRIEKING]

21:52.770 --> 21:54.814
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

22:02.988 --> 22:04.782
What happened?

22:05.658 --> 22:09.495
My magic, I couldn't use it.

22:11.163 --> 22:13.499
LANCELOT: There's something out there.
MERLIN: You saw it?

22:13.666 --> 22:15.835
-When it saw the light, it fled.
-Let's get the horses.

22:16.001 --> 22:18.462
It's not something you can chase
or something you can Kill.

22:18.629 --> 22:19.922
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

22:20.130 --> 22:22.091
We need to get out of here.

22:30.558 --> 22:32.601
[BELL TOLLING]
[PEOPLE SHOUTING]

22:39.316 --> 22:41.735
Gwen. Warn Gaius.

22:41.902 --> 22:43.904
There are more victims by the western gate.

22:45.990 --> 22:48.534
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]
[MAN SCREAMING]

23:19.315 --> 23:20.691
Gaius.

23:21.400 --> 23:22.985
Merlin.

23:24.612 --> 23:26.238
You saw them?

23:28.073 --> 23:31.744
Here, help me. Get me some more sheets.

23:36.749 --> 23:38.459
Merlin?

23:40.002 --> 23:42.296
My magic is useless against them.

23:42.880 --> 23:44.465
I've tried.

23:45.799 --> 23:48.260
| have never felt so powerless.

23:50.971 --> 23:53.015
Something deep inside.

23:53.182 --> 23:56.310
And when it came for me,
| felt this emptiness.

23:58.729 --> 24:00.356
| couldn't breathe.

24:03.067 --> 24:05.444
-I'm scared.
-Merlin.

24:05.903 --> 24:07.738
That's all right.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.617
It's not your fault.

24:15.663 --> 24:19.249
We've suffered 50 dead, maybe more,
mainly in the lower town.

24:19.416 --> 24:21.335
And there's no way of fighting them?

24:21.502 --> 24:23.045
No. Our only weapons are torches.

24:23.212 --> 24:25.422
And the light doesn't kill them,
it only repels them.

24:27.216 --> 24:29.593
-What are they?
GAIUS: The Dorocha, sire.

24:30.219 --> 24:31.804
The spirits of the dead.

24:32.680 --> 24:34.682
On Samhain's eve,
in the time of the old religion...

24:34.848 --> 24:40.104
...the high priestesses would perform
a blood sacrifice and release them.

24:40.270 --> 24:42.064
But who would do such a thing now?

24:42.564 --> 24:45.651
-Morgana.
-You see her hand in this?

24:45.818 --> 24:49.029
We know she was traveling
to the Isle of the Blessed.

24:49.738 --> 24:51.073
How do we defeat these creatures?

24:52.241 --> 24:54.034
| don't know, sire.

24:54.201 --> 24:56.829
No mortal has ever survived their touch.

25:03.460 --> 25:04.503
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

25:11.176 --> 25:12.720
| thought I saw something.

25:15.264 --> 25:17.516
What was it, a spider?

25:25.941 --> 25:27.943
Just pick it up.

25:37.911 --> 25:40.080
Do you want me to get
one of the maids to do it for you?

25:40.247 --> 25:41.749
It's not a joke.

25:45.627 --> 25:47.171
Yeah.

26:02.686 --> 26:03.729
[SIGHS]

26:03.896 --> 26:07.316
You see, Merlin, I could never be like you.

26:07.483 --> 26:09.777
| could never let myself look so spineless.

26:09.943 --> 26:12.946
Oh, you see, I'm different.
| could never let myself look heartless.

26:13.614 --> 26:15.657
-What?
-Well, all right, thoughtless.

26:16.116 --> 26:18.702
-Never.
-Definitely humorless.

26:18.911 --> 26:20.162
That's because you're not funny.

26:20.329 --> 26:21.997
[CHUCKLES]

26:23.248 --> 26:25.375
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

26:29.963 --> 26:32.007
You're not scared?

26:34.468 --> 26:36.553
Oh, I am, Merlin.

26:41.350 --> 26:42.643
Maybe more than you.

27:01.453 --> 27:03.330
[WIND GUSTS]
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

27:28.355 --> 27:30.149
[WHIMPERING]

27:31.942 --> 27:33.986
Hey, hey, hey. It's all right.

27:34.820 --> 27:36.697
It's all right. You're safe now.

27:41.994 --> 27:43.912
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

28:25.287 --> 28:26.830
Thanks.

28:27.164 --> 28:29.499
Couldn't let you have all the glory, could 1?

28:29.917 --> 28:31.335
[CHUCKLES]

28:41.386 --> 28:43.180
GAIUS:
They're coming from across the kingdom.

28:43.347 --> 28:45.390
They're looking to Camelot for protection.

28:46.016 --> 28:47.142
And we will give it to them.

28:47.309 --> 28:49.102
AGRAVAINE:
We cannot house them all.

28:49.269 --> 28:50.812
-We have to try.
AGRAVAINE: How?

28:51.480 --> 28:53.190
We cannot live like this forever, Arthur.

28:53.357 --> 28:55.984
We must find a way
to vanquish these creatures.

28:56.193 --> 28:59.404
Somewhere in all your books,
Gaius, there must be something.

28:59.571 --> 29:01.240
All I'm asking for is a way to fight them.

29:02.241 --> 29:06.161
| fear the Dorocha cannot be defeated
by swords and arrows, sire.

29:06.954 --> 29:09.665
If I am right and the veil
between the worlds is torn...

29:09.831 --> 29:12.751
...then there's only one path open to us:

29:13.794 --> 29:17.214
To travel to the Isle of the Blessed
and repair it.

29:18.006 --> 29:19.132
And how do I do that?

29:19.299 --> 29:22.552
I'm not sure, but for the tear to be created...

29:22.719 --> 29:24.471
...it would have required a blood sacrifice.

29:24.638 --> 29:27.683
To seal it will require another.

29:34.356 --> 29:36.066
We ride before nightfall.

29:39.611 --> 29:41.113
And who will be the sacrifice?

29:44.324 --> 29:46.868
If laying down my life will spare
the people of Camelot...

29:47.035 --> 29:49.246
...then that is what I must do.

30:25.324 --> 30:28.368
-My lady?
-My lord.

30:30.746 --> 30:32.080
| trust you bring me good news.

30:33.790 --> 30:36.877
-Tell me.
-The kingdom is on its knees.

30:38.545 --> 30:40.839
-How terrible.
-Indeed.

30:41.006 --> 30:43.467
-What of the poor people?
-More fall every night.

30:43.884 --> 30:44.926
Such a shame.

30:45.093 --> 30:48.221
You should know that Arthur
intends to vanquish these creatures.

30:48.638 --> 30:49.931
[CHUCKLES]

30:50.640 --> 30:51.850
Impossible.

30:52.017 --> 30:54.353
He makes ready to go
to the Isle of the Blessed as we speak.

30:54.519 --> 30:56.521
And if the Dorocha
don't kill him on the way...

30:56.688 --> 31:00.734
...our brave little lamb
intends to sacrifice himself to repair the veil.

31:09.368 --> 31:10.702
Something's troubling you.

31:12.120 --> 31:13.663
Morgana?

31:14.373 --> 31:16.625
Something the Cailleach said.

31:17.167 --> 31:19.795
She spoke of someone called Emrys...

31:19.961 --> 31:21.838
...called him my doom.

31:22.005 --> 31:24.925
Your doom? What did she mean?

31:25.092 --> 31:26.718
| don't know.

31:26.885 --> 31:29.137
Morgana, we should be celebrating.

31:29.304 --> 31:31.056
Arthur will be dead within the week...

31:31.223 --> 31:35.102
...leaving the throne open
for Camelot's rightful heir.

31:49.324 --> 31:52.285
| have many things I have to thank you for.

31:53.912 --> 31:56.039
You've taught me so much.

31:56.790 --> 31:59.501
Most of all, you have taught me...

32:00.085 --> 32:01.878
...what it is to be a prince.

32:04.214 --> 32:06.842
| hope that this time you'll be proud of me.

32:31.366 --> 32:32.742
Don't leave me.

32:33.952 --> 32:37.330
- I have to, Father.
-Please.

32:54.890 --> 32:57.476
Promise me you'll look after him
when I'm gone.

32:58.977 --> 33:00.520
What is it?

33:02.606 --> 33:04.149
You don't have to go.

33:06.693 --> 33:08.153
| do.

33:09.070 --> 33:11.573
Please, Arthur, take care.

33:12.199 --> 33:15.702
You are precious, not just the kingdom.

33:17.245 --> 33:20.999
-Smile.
- I can't.

33:22.709 --> 33:24.628
Do you remember...

33:26.379 --> 33:28.465
...the first time I kissed you?

33:33.178 --> 33:34.638
There.

33:35.430 --> 33:37.807
That's the memory I want to take with me.

33:54.032 --> 33:56.243
You have to take this. It bears the royal seal.

33:56.409 --> 33:59.371
In my absence, responsibility
for the kingdom rests with you.

33:59.538 --> 34:00.914
What about your father?

34:01.081 --> 34:02.958
Should he die, you're to assume the throne.

34:03.875 --> 34:06.962
-Arthur--
-You're the only person I trust, uncle.

34:09.005 --> 34:11.716
| beg of you, for the sake of the kingdom,
there must be another way.

34:11.882 --> 34:13.260
My mind's made up.

34:16.846 --> 34:18.473
I'm just grateful you're here.

34:24.563 --> 34:26.273
[DOOR OPENS]

34:31.402 --> 34:34.030
Merlin, what are you doing?

34:34.197 --> 34:37.199
-It is my destiny to protect Arthur.
-How?

34:37.367 --> 34:39.536
Your magic is powerless
against the Dorocha.

34:39.703 --> 34:41.871
Then I must sacrifice myself in his place.

34:42.163 --> 34:43.456
No.

34:43.623 --> 34:47.752
My life has always been marked out by destiny.
If this is meant to be...

34:49.920 --> 34:51.130
I'm not afraid.

34:53.049 --> 34:56.011
| will gladly die, Gaius,
knowing that one day...

34:58.555 --> 34:59.931
...Albion will live.

35:33.256 --> 35:34.299
Gwen.

35:34.466 --> 35:38.094
-Will you grant me a favor?
-Anything.

35:40.347 --> 35:41.765
GWEN:
Look after him.

35:42.432 --> 35:43.850
Bring him home.

35:46.770 --> 35:48.897
| will protect him with my life.

35:49.981 --> 35:51.483
You have my promise.

35:53.735 --> 35:54.778
Thank you.

36:03.161 --> 36:05.038
[HORSE WHINNIES]

36:24.933 --> 36:26.851
Elyan, look after the horses.
They need watering.

36:27.018 --> 36:29.312
| need someone to volunteer to get wood.

36:29.479 --> 36:30.730
I'll do that.

36:38.446 --> 36:41.616
You shouldn't be here. You have no powers.

36:41.783 --> 36:43.535
Doesn't matter.

36:43.993 --> 36:45.995
You're not a warrior, Merlin.

36:46.162 --> 36:48.123
| don't want to see you hurt.

36:48.998 --> 36:51.584
If you leave in the morning,
I'll cover with Arthur.

36:53.044 --> 36:55.588
It's your duty to protect Camelot,
no matter what the cost.

36:56.840 --> 36:59.384
Well, it's my duty to protect Arthur.

37:03.555 --> 37:04.889
Surely you can understand that?

37:07.267 --> 37:09.477
| can understand that very well.

37:16.276 --> 37:18.278
[THUNDER RUMBLING IN DISTANCE]

37:23.199 --> 37:25.285
[SWORDS CLANGING]

37:29.581 --> 37:32.083
[VOICES GROANING]

37:36.546 --> 37:38.506
[CAWS]

37:52.395 --> 37:54.439
MORGANA:
Help me, Emrys.

37:54.981 --> 37:56.191
Please.

37:56.357 --> 37:59.152
Is this really what you wanted, Morgana?

37:59.319 --> 38:00.361
Please!

38:00.570 --> 38:02.322
[GASPS]

38:06.701 --> 38:08.369
Emrys.

38:14.501 --> 38:17.796
We need to reach Daelbeth by nightfall.

38:41.986 --> 38:46.407
ARTHUR: Pair off. Find any wood you can.
Let's get the fires burning.

38:48.827 --> 38:51.037
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING NEARBY]

39:03.800 --> 39:05.593
[MAN SCREAMS NEARBY]

39:11.558 --> 39:13.768
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

39:19.524 --> 39:21.276
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

39:21.442 --> 39:23.945
[SCREAMING AND
SHRIEKING CONTINUES]

39:41.379 --> 39:44.299
Let's go! We haven't got enough! Go!

39:51.222 --> 39:52.390
[SPEAKS MAGIC WORDS]

40:05.361 --> 40:07.655
It won't get us through the night.

40:08.656 --> 40:10.867
It'll keep the area safe for a while.

40:24.589 --> 40:29.010
The last one. Maybe we should draw lots,
see who gets some more.

40:29.177 --> 40:31.554
-I'll go.
-You'll need help.

40:31.721 --> 40:35.558
-I'll go with him.
-You sure you're the right person?

40:36.059 --> 40:38.186
And since when have you known
how to collect firewood?

40:38.353 --> 40:40.730
[MEN CHUCKLING]

40:51.199 --> 40:52.784
[LOUD SHRIEKING]

40:52.992 --> 40:54.285
Merlin, look out!

40:56.454 --> 40:57.830
Let's go!

41:07.215 --> 41:08.341
[SHRIEKING]

41:11.219 --> 41:14.180
-They should have been back by now.
-Someone needs to go and look for them.

41:14.347 --> 41:17.558
-We've only got one torch between us.
-Who's coming?

41:21.980 --> 41:23.606
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

41:32.907 --> 41:34.784
[SHIVERING]

41:37.704 --> 41:40.123
-It's cold.
-Right.

41:41.374 --> 41:43.292
-You're not feeling it?
-I...

41:44.252 --> 41:47.255
You know, Merlin, you're braver
than I give you credit for.

41:47.422 --> 41:48.589
Really? Was that a compliment?

41:49.465 --> 41:50.717
Don't be stupid.

41:50.883 --> 41:52.468
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

42:00.309 --> 42:01.978
[DOROCHA SHRIEKS]

42:06.691 --> 42:08.818
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

42:10.528 --> 42:12.780
[SHIVERING AND PANTING]

42:21.122 --> 42:22.957
All the things I've faced...

42:24.375 --> 42:26.335
...I've never worried about dying.

42:27.253 --> 42:29.213
| don't think you should now.

42:31.674 --> 42:33.051
Sometimes you puzzle me.

42:34.385 --> 42:37.055
-You never fathomed me out?
-No.

42:38.765 --> 42:42.393
| always thought that if things had been
different, we'd have been good friends.

42:43.311 --> 42:44.353
Yeah.

42:45.521 --> 42:48.107
That's if you hadn't been such an arrogant,
pompous dollop-head.

42:48.316 --> 42:49.901
[CHUCKLES]

42:53.279 --> 42:55.323
We'll defeat the Dorocha.

42:55.531 --> 42:57.742
We will, Arthur. Together.

43:00.119 --> 43:01.537
Well, I appreciate that.

43:04.624 --> 43:06.167
You know, you're a brave man, Merlin.

43:08.628 --> 43:09.712
Between battles.

43:09.879 --> 43:11.339
[CHUCKLES]

43:14.175 --> 43:16.302
You don't know how many times
I've saved your life.

43:16.511 --> 43:17.970
[CHUCKLES]

43:18.137 --> 43:21.516
If I ever become king,
I'm going to have you made court jester.

43:21.724 --> 43:24.185
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

43:25.311 --> 43:27.522
[DOROCHA SHRIEKING]

43:37.240 --> 43:39.033
[SHRIEKING]

43:42.703 --> 43:45.123
They say the darkest hour
is just before the dawn.

43:45.289 --> 43:48.793
-It's pretty dark right now.
-It can't be long then.

43:48.960 --> 43:50.461
[SHRIEKING]

43:55.049 --> 43:56.634
ARTHUR:
Merlin, no!

44:10.398 --> 44:11.941
What happened?

44:22.910 --> 44:24.745
MALE VOICE:
Merlin.

44:28.124 --> 44:31.752
The Dorocha cannot be allowed
to remain in this world.

44:31.919 --> 44:35.214
The sundered veil must be restored.

44:37.550 --> 44:40.219
MERLIN: Arthur intends
to sacrifice himself to heal the veil.

44:41.554 --> 44:42.763
| must take his place.

44:42.972 --> 44:45.933
Merlin, you must not do this.

45:24.513 --> 45:26.515
[English - US - SDH]
